From http://labjack.com/support/linux-and-mac-os-x-drivers 2012-04-14 instructions on how to install the latest version of labjack drivers on Linux.  Go to the source for OSX instructions.

sudo apt-get install build-essential
sudo apt-get install libusb-1.0-0-dev
sudo apt-get install git-core
git clone git://github.com/labjack/exodriver.git
cd exodriver/liblabjackusb/
make
sudo make install
cd ..
sudo cp 10-labjack.rules /etc/udev/rules.d/.
sudo udevadm control --reload-rules
cd ../..
git clone git://github.com/labjack/LabJackPython.git
cd LabJackPython/
sudo python setup.py install

Now you should be able to use it, try:
ipython
>>> import u3
>>> d = u3.U3()
>>> d.configU3()
ipython

